    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS, BUMPER AND RUNNING BOARDS - MXT - REMOVE AND INSTALL - FENDER EXTENSIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>FENDER EXTENSIONS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The fender extensions are part of the body splash protection system. The wheel well openings in the
                fender extensions have been designed to provide splash and spray protection. These protect the lower
                front of the cab from splash and road debris kicked up by the front tires, and it also keeps the step
                cleaner.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension - Removal</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Release hood latches on each side of the hood and tilt the hood assembly forward.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901339" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901339.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 39. Fender Extension</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the two lower fender extension bolts (Item 2, Figure 40) from bracket (Item 3,
                    Figure 40).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901340" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901340.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 40. Lower Fender Extension Bracket and Bolts</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>2. LOWER FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. LOWER FENDER EXTENSION MOUNTING BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the centering bolt (Item 4, Figure 41) from bracket (Item 5, Figure 41).</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901341" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901341.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 41. Fender Extension Centering Bolt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>4. FENDER EXTENSION CENTERING BOLT</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. FENDER EXTENSION BRACKET</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the top fender extension mounting bolt (Item 6, Figure 42) and fender extension
                    (Item 1, Figure 42) from vehicle.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f0901342" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0901342.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="304px"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Top Fender Extension Mounting Bolt</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. FENDER EXTENSION</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. TOP MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Follow same procedure to remove opposite side fender extension.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Fender Extension - Installation</title>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The fender extension installation procedure should be done in conjunction with 3.2 HOOD
                        STOP/FENDER EXTENSION ADJUSTMENT.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install fender extension (Item 1, Figures 39 and 42) on vehicle and secure with top
                    mounting bolt (Item 6, Figure 42).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the fender extension with the mounting holes on the lower fender bracket (Item 3,
                    Figure 40) and secure with two mounting bolts (Item 2, Figure 40).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install centering bolt (Item 4, Figure 41) into bracket (Item 5, Figure 41).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Torque the mounting bolts. See torque chart.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
